K-PS2-1                                                                                                                                    ND Science Standards
Motion and Stability: Forces and Interactions
              Performance Standard               Conduct an investigation to compare the effects of different strengths or
                        K-PS2-1                  different directions of pushes and pulls on the motion of an object.
 Clarification Statement                            Examples of pushes or pulls could include a string attached to an object being pulled, a person pushing an
                                                    object, a person stopping a rolling ball, and two objects colliding and pushing on each other.
 Assessment Boundary                                Assessment is limited to different relative strengths or different directions, but not both at the same time.
                                                    Assessment does not include non-contact pushes or pulls such as those produced by magnets.
 Disciplinary Core Ideas                            Science & Engineering Practices                                       Crosscutting Concepts
