and directions. Pushing or pulling on an object    peers.                                                                 gather evidence to support or refute
can change the speed or direction of its motion                                                                           student ideas about causes.
and can start or stop it.
PS2.B: Types of Interactions
-When objects touch or collide, they push on one
another and can change motion.
PS3.C: Relationship Between Energy and Forces
-A bigger push or pull makes things speed up or
slow down more quickly.
