3-PS2-1                                                                                                                                   ND Science Standards
Motion & Stability: Forces & Interactions
              Performance Standard                Plan and conduct an investigation to prove the effects of balanced and
                        3-PS2-1                   unbalanced forces on the motion of an object.
 Clarification Statement                           Examples could include an unbalanced force on one side of a ball can make it start moving; and balanced
                                                   forces pushing on a box from both sides will not produce any motion at all.
 Assessment Boundary                               Assessment is limited to one variable at a time: number, size, or direction of forces.
