MS-ESS1-2                                                                                                                                     ND Science Standards
Earth’s Place in the Universe
              Performance Standard                 Develop and use a model to describe the role of gravity in the motions
                       MS-ESS1-2                   within galaxies and the solar system.
 Clarification Statement                           Emphasis for the model is on gravity as the force that holds together the solar system and Milky Way galaxy
                                                   and controls orbital motions within them. Examples of models can be physical (such as the analogy of
                                                   distance along a football field or computer visualizations of elliptical orbits) or conceptual (such as
                                                   mathematical proportions relative to the size of familiar objects such as students’ school or state).
 Assessment Boundary                               Assessment does not include Kepler’s Laws of orbital motion or the apparent retrograde motion of the
                                                   planets as viewed from Earth.
