 Clarification Statement                          Emphasis is on the analysis of data from Earth-based instruments, space-based telescopes, and spacecraft to
                                                  determine similarities and differences among solar system objects. Examples of scale properties include the
                                                  sizes of an object’s layers (such as crust and atmosphere), surface features (such as volcanoes), and
