 of interconnected ocean currents.                 5. Using mathematical and computational thinking                  and information flows within systems.
                                                   6. Constructing explanations and designing solutions
 ESS2.D: Weather and Climate                       7. Engaging in argument from evidence
 -Weather and climate are influenced by            8. Obtaining, evaluating, and communicating information
 interactions involving sunlight, the ocean, the
 atmosphere, ice, landforms, and living things.
 These interactions vary with latitude, altitude,
 and local and regional geography, all of which
 can affect oceanic and atmospheric flow
 patterns.
