              Performance Standard            Construct a scientific explanation based on evidence for how
                      MS-LS1-5                environmental and genetic factors influence the growth of organisms.
 Clarification Statement                       Examples of local environmental conditions could include availability of food, light, space, and water
                                               (photosynthesis). Examples of genetic factors could include large breed cattle and species of grass affecting
                                               growth of organisms. Examples of evidence could include drought decreasing plant growth, fertilizer
                                               increasing plant growth, different varieties of plant seeds growing at different rates in different conditions,
                                               and fish growing larger in large ponds than they do in small ponds.
 Assessment Boundary                           Assessment does not include genetic mechanisms, gene regulation, or biochemical processes.
