HS-LS4-2                                                                                                                                    ND Science Standards
BIOLOGICAL EVOLUTION: UNITY AND DIVERSITY
       Performance Standard                  Construct an explanation based on evidence that the process of biological evolution
                 HS-LS4-2                    primarily results from four factors: (1) the potential for a species to increase in number,
                                             (2) the heritable genetic variation of individuals in a species due to mutation and sexual
                                             reproduction, (3) competition for limited resources, and (4) the proliferation of those
                                             organisms that are better able to survive and reproduce in the environment.
 Clarification Statement                            Emphasis is on using evidence to explain the influence each of the four factors has on the number of
                                                    organisms, behaviors, morphology, or physiology in terms of ability to compete for limited resources and
                                                    subsequent survival of individuals and adaptation of species. Examples of evidence could include
                                                    mathematical models such as simple distribution graphs and proportional reasoning.
 Assessment Boundary                                Assessment does not include other mechanisms of evolution, such as genetic drift, gene flow through
                                                    migration, and co-evolution.
 Disciplinary Core Ideas                            Science & Engineering Practices                                         Crosscutting Concepts
