 between organisms in a population and (2)          4. Analyzing and interpreting data                                      correlation and make claims about
 variation in the expression of that genetic        5. Using mathematical and computational thinking                        specific causes.
 information — that is, trait variation — that      6. Constructing explanations and designing solutions
 leads to differences in performance among              • Construct an explanation based on valid and reliable
 individuals.                                               evidence obtained from a variety of sources and the
 LS4.C: Adaptation                                          assumption that theories and laws that describe the
 Evolution is a consequence of the interaction              natural world operate today as they did in the past and will
