                                                  of atoms.
 Clarification Statement                          Physical Science: Examples of properties that could be predicted from patterns could include metals,
                                                  nonmetals, metalloids, number of valence electrons, types of bonds formed, or atomic mass. Emphasis is
                                                  on main group elements.
                                                  Chemistry: Examples of properties that could be predicted from patterns could include reactivity of
                                                  metals, types of bonds formed, numbers of bonds formed, atomic radius, atomic mass, or reactions with
                                                  oxygen. Emphasis is on main group elements and qualitative understanding of the relative trends of
                                                  ionization energy and electronegativity.
