              Performance Standard              Use mathematical representations to support the claim that atoms, and
                      HS-PS1-7                  therefore mass, are conserved during a chemical reaction.
 Clarification Statement                         Physical Science: Emphasis is on using mathematical ideas as they relate to balancing reactions to
                                                 communicate the proportional relationships between masses of atoms in the reactants and the products.
                                                 Emphasis is on assessing students’ use of mathematical thinking and not on memorization.
                                                 Chemistry: Emphasis is on using mathematical ideas as they relate to balancing reactions and
                                                 stoichiometry to communicate the proportional relationships between masses of atoms in the reactants
                                                 and the products. Emphasis is on assessing students’ use of mathematical thinking and not on
                                                 memorization.
 Assessment Boundary                             Assessment is limited to balancing chemical equations. Assessment does not include complex reactions.
