              Performance Standard                  Evaluate evidence of the past and current movements of continental and
                       HS-ESS1-5                    oceanic crust and the theory of plate tectonics to explain the ages of crustal
                                                    rocks.
 Clarification Statement                                           Emphasis is on the ability of plate tectonics to explain the ages of crustal rocks. Examples
                                                                   include evidence of the ages of oceanic crust increasing with distance from mid-ocean
                                                                   ridges (a result of plate spreading) and the ages of North American continental crust
                                                                   decreasing with distance away from a central ancient core of the continental plate (a
                                                                   result of past plate interactions).
