Content Resource: K Grade Physical Science K-PS2-1 Motion and Stability: Forces and Interactions
Observable features of the student performance by the end of the grade:
   Identifying the phenomenon to be investigated
1     With guidance, students collaboratively identify the phenomenon under investigation, which includes the following idea: the effect caused by different
   a
      strengths and directions of pushes and pulls on the motion of an object.
      With guidance, students collaboratively identify the purpose of the investigation, which includes gathering evidence to support or refute student ideas about
1 b
      causes of the phenomenon by comparing the effects of different strengths of pushes and pulls on the motion of an object.
   Identifying the evidence to address this purpose of the investigation
2.    With guidance, students collaboratively develop an investigation plan to investigate the relationship between the strength and direction of pushes and pulls
   a
      and the motion of an object (i.e., qualitative measures or expressions of strength and direction; e.g., harder, softer, descriptions* of “which way”).
      Students describe* how the observations they make connect to the purpose of the investigation, including how the observations of the effects on object
2. b
      motion allow causal relationships between pushes and pulls and object motion to be determined
2 c Students predict the effect of the push of pull on the motion of the object, based on prior experiences.
   Conducting the investigation
   a In the investigation plan, students describe*:
      i. The object whose motion will be investigated.
      ii. What will be in contact with the object to cause the push or pull.
3
      iii. The relative strengths of the push or pull that will be applied to the object to start or stop its motion or change its speed.
      iv. The relative directions of the push or pull that will be applied to the object.
      v. How the motion of the object will be observed and recorded.
      vi. How the push or pull will be applied to vary strength or direction.
4     Collecting the data
      According to the investigation plan, students collaboratively make observations that would allow them to compare the effect on the motion of the object
   a.
      caused by changes in the strength or direction of the pushes and pulls and record their data.
