    Students describe* the evidence to be collected, including:
  a i. How well the model/prototype performs against the given criteria and constraints.
2
    ii. Specific aspects of the prototype or model that do not meet one or more of the criteria or constraints (i.e., failure points or difficulties).
    iii. Aspects of the model/prototype that can be improved to better meet the criteria and constraints.
